<subSubSection id="A26C929A6CB0D038762B6CE197B5B4DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="EB8B3456CFC3027912034B96E0EACBBD" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9425BE2529D23D027201CF7C8B56E804" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Shell with very wide orifice; alae broadly-triangular with summits oblique; scutum folded longitudinally, articular ridge slightly prominent, deep pit for adductor muscle; tergum beaked, with prominent articular ridge, spur very broadly rounded; inner side of scutum and tergum orange-coloured.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="230A7E3F690AD27DE38C4C1FE77BE77B" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="description">
<paragraph id="5BC0A8D2F85B4EFBE97ACA5D919C96E9" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1EBC5A3481AB10F4905A061A43DA8520" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Shell yellowish, conical, with six plates. Orifice diamond-shaped; scutum triangular elongated with protruding growth-ridges; tergum smaller than scutum, apex beaked, carinal margin rounded, growth-ridges less distinct than on scutum. Cirrus I with unequal rami (anterior ramus: 8-segmented; posterior ramus: 12-segmented), dense long setae on surface areas. Cirrus II with equal rami, dense long setae. Cirri IV-VI with equal rami with numerous segments; segments almost without exception furnished with two pairs very long, stiff, needle-like spines along inner faces. Measurements of specimen: basal length of shell 14.32 mm, orifice length 8.00 mm, carinal height 12.39 mm, orifice width 6.49 mm, basal width 13.76 mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BD92D1728BDD6F09A54197BFB153A61D" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="D483F023E3C72DC23E2FF393FFDC3BAA" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B035F8BAD6596ED50C725942C1590314" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">
Arafura Sea, Indonesia; 205-560 m depth (
<bibRefCitation id="A383B8C5018131A7E2970622C0C239E1" author="Jones, DS" journalOrPublisher="Raffles Bulletin of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" pagination="241 - 311" refId="B91" refString="Jones, DS, Hosie, AM, 2016. A checklist of the barnacles (Cirripedia: Thoracica) of Singapore and neighbouring waters. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology 34: 241 - 311" title="A checklist of the barnacles (Cirripedia: Thoracica) of Singapore and neighbouring waters." volume="34" year="2016">Jones and Hosie 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In this study, 
<taxonomicName id="46284FCE8856F8FDFB9E7EC699896D6A" authorityName="Hoek" authorityYear="1913" class="Maxillopoda" family="Bathylasmatidae" genus="Hexelasma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hexelasma arafurae" order="Sessilia" pageId="0" pageNumber="649" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="arafurae">
<emphasis id="76A5C8CFE897F31FB0C4FD089254A5A9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="649">Hexelasma arafurae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found at Kei Islands, Indonesia.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
